 = f\"\n               :informal-clause \"Certifies Stage 1(b): the continuous bijection f is a homeomorphism.\"\n               :role :main-theorem}\n              {:formal-name \"isCompact_image\"\n               :formal-statement \"∀ {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y]\\n   {K : Set X} {f : X → Y}, IsCompact K → Continuous f →\\n   IsCompact (f '' K)\"\n               :informal-clause \"Part (a): establishes that continuous images of compact sets are compact, used to show f is a closed map.\"\n               :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\nSummary of current state for apm-t92J02:\n\n- Planning artifacts are in place. `proof-plan.edn` now records the goal, compactness/closed-map key terms, and the Lean strategy targeting `image_compact_and_homeo`, with stage-status already marked Stage 1/2 done and later stages pending.\n- `formal-alignment.edn` ties the informal claim (“continuous bijection from compact to Hausdorff is a homeomorphism”) to a concrete Lean target plus the helper lemma `isCompact_image`, so the HtDP sanity check is satisfied.\n- `execute.md` is still just the scaffold text—Stages 1–4 haven’t been written. `changelog.edn` only logs workspace initialization; no subsequent progress entries yet. The Lean files under `ApmCanaries/Frames/T92J02/...` have not been populated.\n\nNext steps:\n\n1. Draft Stage 1 (reader proof) and Stage 2 (dependency narrative) in `execute.md`, then log the work in `changelog.edn`.\n2. Formal phase: implement the Mathlib-backed statements in `/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T92J02/Apm_v2_t92J02_1775008678104/Main.lean`, running `lake build`, and update Stage 3 plus the changelog.\n3. Finish by syncing the informal write-up with the formal proof for Stage 4 and closing out the changelog entry.\n\nLet me know when you want me to pick up these next actions.\n\n---\n\nUpdates complete.\n\n- Filled every Stage section in `execute.md` (t92J02/…/execute.md), including the required “Why it’s hard